She goes FAST!

Making free throws

She goes...AIRBALL!

Taking a doze.

She goes zzzz!
She goes zzzz!

Lyrics
With so much drama in the 4, 5, 6
I'll droppa comma in a sentence like a ton of bricks
There's alotta instances when I gotta use one
BLAZER FRESH is here to eliminate the comma blues son.

I use a comma, i use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use one!

I USE A COMMA to separate three or more words in a list.

I'm maxin, relaxin', and cool. You get the gist?

I USE A COMMA  after introductory words, such as yes and well:

Yes, I am wearing cologne. How can you tell?

I USE A COMMA  to separate adjectives, 2 or more
I'll droppa comma in a sentence like a ton of bricks
There's alotta instances when I gotta use one
Blazer Fresh is here to eliminate the comma blues son.

Arnstar is a charming, fun fellow on the dance floor.

I USE A COMMA before a conjunction to join independent clauses.

I like enormous words, and I like pauses.

With so much drama in the 4, 5, 6
I use a comma, i use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I would use a comma

I USE A COMMA on either side of an appositive.

Xavier, the optimist, is always so positive.

I USE A COMMA  when I address someone, it helps us understand:

Excuse me, Rasheem, when you raise the roof, put up your hands!

I USE A COMMA  between the name of a city and its state:

San Francisco, California, has's got this bridge—- the Golden Gate!

I USE A COMMA  when I quote:

She said, "I only hike up mountains with my mountain goat."

I USE A COMMA  when I write the date between the day and year:

January 1, 1735. Happy birthday, PAUL REVERE!

With so much drama in the 4, 5, 6
I'll droppa comma in a sentence like a TON OF BRICKS
There's alotta instances when I gotta use one
Blazer Fresh is here to eliminate the comma blues son.

I use a comma, i use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma…

Hold the applause! You can also use a comma after a dependent clause!
Ohhhhh

When I watch movies, I like to eat seaweed. 

When I  make smoothies, I put in tons of flax seeds. 

While you were out, all I thought about was commas.

When spring break comes, I wanna go to the Bahamas!

With so much drama in the 4, 5, 6
I'll droppa comma in a sentence like a TON OF BRICKS
There's alotta instances when I gotta use one
Blazer Fresh is here to eliminate the comma blues son.

I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma, I use a comma…

videos.description:
Growing up in today's society can be very challenging. Half of all kids have experienced serious emotional trauma - bullying, violence, family problems, and financial stress.

Meet Aamon, a 10-year-old in the 4th grade at Stuckey Elementary in Redford, MI, right outside of Detroit. According to his teacher, Ms. Holdorf, Aamon had a rough childhood. He changed schools multiple times, and was angry, removed, disruptive, and not doing well academically. When Ms. Holdorf began using GoNoodle, Aamon began to change and so did her entire class. This is Aamon's story and how GoNoodle helped Aamon with mindfulness and movement.

videos.title: Road Trip USA With Blazer Fresh + More Songs for Kids | GoNoodle
videos.description:
Can you name all 50 states in the United States? Come join GoNoodle as we head on a road trip using the United States map and dance and sing along with Blazer Fresh as we sing the Road Trippin' song!

Subscribe To GoNoodle for more FUN kids videos: https://www.youtube.com/c/GoNoodle?sub_confirmation=1

Lyrics 
My country tis of thee.
Sweet land of liberty,
Of thee I sing…
(spoken): Nerdy By Nature is road trippin...yeah!

Let’s go!
My country tis of thee,
We went to see ALL FIFTY STATES.
We just got in the car,
And drove really far,
We took a lotta BATHROOM BREAKS.

In every single state we saw a lot of really awesome stuff
So pack a bag,
Start the engine, buckle up,
WE'RE RIDIN TOUGH.
Let’s do it!

Where to first? Oh, you know we got to stop in the Big Apple.
New York’s pizza was first rate
Connecticut is the nutmeg state
in Rhode Island we saw a whale
Massachusetts we walked the Freedom Trail
In Maine the lobster we did try
New Hampshire’s motto is live free or die
Vermont has tons of dairy cows
Ohio means beautiful river - WOW!
I had no idea!

Let’s go!
Michigan makes dope car parts
Kentucky’s bluegrass warmed our hearts
Indiana is the Hoosier State  (ILLINOIS)
in Missouri we saw the midwest's gate
Iowa’s corn was better than ever
Wisconsin had the freshest cheddar
in Minnesota it was super cold  
in Nebraska lots of beef was sold!

In South Dakota we saw Mt. Rushmore
North Dakota was right next door
Montana had a real big sky
Washington’s named for a super nice guy
George Washington? That’s my guy right there.
Oregon’s fishing was really good
California’s home to Hollywood  
Selfie!

In Nevada’s we swam the Hoover Dam
Arizona’s had snakes  - OH MAN!!!
Watch out!
AH! Snakes!
in Utah we saw the Great Salt Lake
But we didn’t stay long cuz we still had 23 states!

WE'RE RIDIN TOUGH
In Idaho there was a lot of snow
In Wyoming we ran from a BUFFALO!
Colorado had the dopest slopes
In New Mexico we used telescopes - WOW!
Anybody seen ET?

The Texas chili was very hot
And Oklahoma was shaped like a pot (KANSAS)
in Arkansas we played with a poodle
in Tennessee we visited GONOODLE!  
What’s up Mr. Catman?
GO NOODLE!

Mississippi! Can you spell it? M-I-S-S-I-S-S-I-P-P-I …wait
That was pretty fly!  
in Louisiana we heard jazz play
in Alabama we ate shrimp all day
in Florida there was tons of gators
and we were all like: SEE YOU LATER!
See ya later!
Oh! Alligator!

Georgia was so nice and peachy
South Carolina had sandy beachies
in West Virginia there was coal for days
in North Carolina we saw the Panthers play - TOUCH DOWN!
in Virginia clams were all we ate.
DC was great - but it’s not a state!
(Wait what!? Oh right! I knew that, it’s not a state)
in Maryland we cast a fishing line!
And Delaware’s water gap was FOYNE!

At the New Jersey shore we found dope shells
in Pennsylvania we saw the Liberty BELL!
Real quick let's hit the airport  
I know I didn't ask ya'
We've got to see the last two states
HAWAII AND ALASKA!
HAWAII AND ALASKA!

Hey man, that was fun
We gotta do that again
Now where ya’all...I didn’t mean right now!
Why ya’ll leaving?
I didn’t mean right now!
Alright, I’m coming, I’m coming.
